Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Kedar Jadhav, out Lbw!! Kedar Jadhav's out lbw. Another review from CSK: Legal delivery and there seems to be no bat involved. Has it done too much though, the googly? He's struck in line with off and there's another umpire's call on hitting. Shaving the top of leg peg. OUT!! A rather simple set-up this from Rashid, bowled the wrong 'un and gave it ample flight to draw Jadhav on the front foot. The batsman clearly didn't pick the variation and his forward stride meant he was struck adjacent to middle and leg. Kedar Jadhav lbw b Rashid Khan 1(2)

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Raina, out Lbw!! Raina has been given out lbw off Rashid. CSK review: Fair delivery, looks to be pitching in line and no bat involved. Umpire's call on hitting and he has to go. Hasn't been at his fluent best and this shot is a firm proof of that. Just looks to slog without having a real sense of where the ball pitched and he loses his shape in the process, swings way too early and Rashid's floaty legbreak clonks him in front of middle. Technology shows it to be brushing the leg bail. Just enough. Raina lbw b Rashid Khan 13(13) [4s-2]
